{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 23:10:12.888589", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and view\\n- Topology: 3-stage Clos (EBGP) with one super-spine (AS 65000), two spines, and two leaves. Each leaf hosts one /24 toward an attached host.\\n- Hosts in focus: pc_0_0 (attached to leaf_router_0_0), pc_0_1 (attached to leaf_router_0_1).\\n\\n1) Anomaly detection\\n- End-to-end reachability tests show the fabric is broadly healthy, but pc_0_1 exhibits complete loss of connectivity:\\n  - Automated reachability matrix recorded “unknown” for pc_0_1 as a source.\\n  - Direct tests from pc_0_1:\\n    - ping 10.0.0.1 (its configured default gateway) fails 100% loss.\\n    - ping 10.0.1.1 (the leaf it is physically connected to) returns “Destination Host Unreachable.”\\n- Suspicious result: pc_0_0 → pc_0_1 is reported as successful with very low RTT. However, both pc_0_0 and pc_0_1 share the same IP (10.0.0.2), so that test actually pinged the local address on pc_0_0 and does not reflect real inter-host reachability.\\n\\n2) Fault localization\\n- Control plane: All EBGP sessions across the fabric are established and carrying full routes:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0: 8 neighbors up; receiving 31 prefixes; FRR “show ip route” has complete coverage for all 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24 networks.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1: 8 neighbors up; receiving 31 prefixes; also shows full 10.x.x.0/24 coverage.\\n  - spines and super-spine have their BGP adjacencies up and routing tables populated. ECMP is present at the super-spine toward downstream prefixes.\\n- Data plane: pc_0_0 has correct local connectivity and can reach remote subnets (e.g., 10.1.3.2).\\n- The connectivity failure is localized to the end host pc_0_1 and its directly connected segment, not the fabric.\\n\\n3) Root cause analysis\\n- Host IP configuration inconsistency on pc_0_1:\\n  - pc_0_1 is configured with IP 10.0.0.2/24 and default via 10.0.0.1.\\n  - Physical attachment is to leaf_router_0_1, whose host-facing SVI is 10.0.1.1/24 (leaf_router_0_1:eth8).\\n  - Therefore, pc_0_1 is on the 10.0.1.0/24 subnet but configured as if it were on 10.0.0.0/24. This causes:\\n    - Wrong subnet and gateway for its L2 domain.\\n    - Inability to ARP for 10.0.0.1 (no L2 adjacency to that gateway) and no direct L3 adjacency to 10.0.1.1 because the host believes it is on a different subnet.\\n- Duplicate IP address:\\n  - pc_0_0 also has 10.0.0.2/24. This creates an IP duplicate across two different L3 subnets (10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24) and invalidates reachability tests targeting “pc_0_1” (they inadvertently target pc_0_0’s IP).\\n- Leaf interfaces corroborate the issue:\\n  - leaf_router_0_1: host-facing interface (10.0.1.1/24) shows almost no traffic, consistent with the host being misaddressed and not properly communicating on that subnet.\\n\\nEvidence highlights\\n- pc_0_0 net config: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1 (matches its leaf 10.0.0.1) — healthy.\\n- pc_0_1 net config: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1 (does not match its leaf 10.0.1.1) — misconfigured.\\n- pc_0_1 ping tests: 100% loss to 10.0.0.1 and “Destination Host Unreachable” to 10.0.1.1.\\n- leaf_router_0_1 host-facing SVI: 10.0.1.1/24; routing table shows 10.0.1.0/24 directly connected.\\n- Fabric BGP: All sessions established on both leaves, spines, and super-spine with full distribution of 10.x.x.0/24 routes.\\n\\nAssessment\\n- Overall fabric health: Normal; EBGP sessions up; routing tables complete; inter-subnet reachability from correctly configured hosts is good.\\n- Abnormal behavior: pc_0_1 is unreachable due to host-side IP misconfiguration and IP duplication with pc_0_0.\\n- Faulty device: pc_0_1 (end-host NIC/IP configuration).\\n- Root cause: Wrong IP address/subnet/default gateway on pc_0_1 (should be in 10.0.1.0/24 to match its leaf; currently set to 10.0.0.2/24 with gateway 10.0.0.1), causing both an IP duplicate and mismatched gateway/subnet, breaking connectivity., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='c6307b76-c1e4-44f5-be24-1331e29936da'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
